This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with machine translation, a subfield of natural language processing. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel variational recurrent neural machine translation model, which falls under the category of neural machine translation models, a popular research area in cs.CL. 

The paper also involves the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper introduces a neural posterior approximator and uses a reparameterization technique, which are techniques commonly used in the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Finally, the paper involves experiments on Chinese-English and English-German translation tasks, which may fall under the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as computer vision techniques are often used in image-to-text translation tasks.
